The programs in this directory are those developed in Chapter 3 of the book.
The spl_date* programs are successively more enhanced implementations of the
date command. The remaining programs are demonstrations of how to use 
variouse locale-bed functions.

Their order in the book is as follows.

spl_date1.c
spl_date2.c
spl_date3.c
spl_date4.c
strcoll_demo.c
strfmon_demo.c
nl_langinfo_demo1.c
nl_langinfo_demo2.c
newlocale_demo.c

The shell script named testspl_date3.sh is teh script used to test the
spl_date3.c program.
